<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF108-288-450  </DOCNO><DOCID>08 288 450.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Information Week  March 26 1990 n263 p67(1).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Old hand retires. (Glenn H. Haney, US Department of Agriculture)andM;</TITLE><TEXT><ABSTRACT>Glenn Haney, director of information resource management (IRM) forthe US Department of Agriculture, is retiring after eight years inthe position.andP;  Generally, IRM directors hold their posts anaverage of four years.andP;  Haney, however, feels his departmentbenefited from his 'longevity' because they would not haveaccomplished the level of distributed processing with higherturnover.andP;  Haney postponed his retirement until his superior movedto another post as director of the Federal Quality Institute.andO;Haney feels his largest accomplishments include establishing thefirst civilian nationwide data communications network, automating90 percent of the department's 15,000 field offices andimplementing electronic dissemination of computer-basedinformation.andP;  Haney now plans to become a consultant.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Topic:     United States. Department of AgricultureRetirement.andO;Feature:   illustrationportrait.andO;Caption:   Glenn H. Haney. (portrait)Person:    Haney, H. Glen (resignation, retirement, etc.).andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>